# ============================================================
#  Git Commit Message Template
#  Project: MASkillBlender Project Page
#  Usage: Automatically loaded by Git during `git commit`
# ============================================================
#
# Format:
#   <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# Example:
#   content(abstract): refine paragraph wording
#
#   Tighten the second paragraph and emphasize the central claim.
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Commit Types:
#   feat      - Add new feature or section
#   fix       - Fix a bug or broken rendering
#   docs      - Documentation or README
#   style     - CSS or visual adjustments without behavior change
#   refactor  - Restructure HTML or assets without content change
#   chore     - Maintenance, cleanup, minor updates
#   revert    - Revert previous commit
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Suggested Scopes:
#   content   - Abstract, captions, or textual content
#   layout    - HTML structure and section ordering
#   style     - CSS and visual styling
#   assets    - Images, videos, and other media
#   meta      - <head>, SEO tags, favicon
#   deps      - Vendored third-party libraries (Bulma, FontAwesome, etc.)
#   deploy    - GitHub Pages configuration
#   docs      - README and developer notes
#   chore     - Maintenance and minor cleanup
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Template:
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

# Description: explain what and why changes were made.
<body>

# End of commit message
# ============================================================
